snippet.textDisplay: Don't know why ole is saying it took klopp four years to get it right at Liverpool. It never took him four years. He was named the manager towards the end of 2015 and two years later they signed van dijk and after that they have been a top side since so it actually took him two years. Solskjaer has been at United for over a year. Another year and United will still not be anywhere near the level Liverpool were at two years ago. World class defender, world class midfielder and world class winger. Those are the three players United need just to get to where Liverpool were two years ago and then maybe when or if Rashford becomes a world class striker and the players around him perform week in week out, United could be as good as city or Liverpool but no that's not gunna happen because United rotate managers and if solskjaer isn't at United next season then sign Pochettino or Allegri. But Pochettino likes to work with a small squad and I prefer squad depth like man city have because if city squad depth was like spurs, then they wouldn't be 2nd place. They would be 4th or lower
